remarks: Severity is high for juvenile PSMEM (~8-18 years), low for majority of mature and seedling boles, with some exceptional individuals. Swiss Needle Cast. Chlorosis and needle loss of 2-4th year growth, as well as ascomata observed on PSMEM throughout the site. Young stands (planted ~2000-2012) are most obviously affected, in some cases > 95% of individuals indicating and >50% retaining <2nd year growth. Rarely, mature trees observed with <2nd year growth.

dateRemarks: Sometime prior to this date, the plant arrived.
remarks: First noticed in distructive sampling area at a plot at this site. It may have occured onsite previously but not in any of our plots until now.

The Red Butte Reservoir is downstream of the entire research reach. More information can be found at https://dwrapps.utah.gov/fishstocking/Fish.

In 2020, Utah Division of Wildlife Resources reported that 2001 Bonneville Cutthroat Trout, 2.27 inches in length on average, were stocked in Red Butte Reservoir on October 12th. The Red Butte Reservoir is downstream of the entire research reach. More information can be found at https://dwrapps.utah.gov/fishstocking/Fish.

In 2021, Utah Division of Wildlife Resources reported that 1646 Bonneville Cutthroat Trout, 2.43 inches in length on average, were stocked in Red Butte Reservoir on October 13th. 833 Bonneville Cutthroat Trout 2.43 inches in length on average were stocked in Red Butte Creek. The Red Butte Reservoir is downstream of the entire research reach. More information can be found at https://dwrapps.utah.gov/fishstocking/Fish.

In 2022, Utah Division of Wildlife Resources reported that 50 Bonneville Cutthroat Trout, 6.22 inches in length on average, were stocked in Red Butte Creek on June 8th. More information can be found at https://dwrapps.utah.gov/fishstocking/Fish.

In 2022, Utah Division of Wildlife Resources reported that 2331 Bonneville Cutthroat Trout, 2.09 inches in length on average, were stocked in Red Butte Reservoir on September 21st. The Red Butte Reservoir is downstream of the entire research reach. More information can be found at https://dwrapps.utah.gov/fishstocking/Fish.

In 2023, Utah Division of Wildlife Resources reported that 991 Bonneville cutthroat trout, 3.18 inches in length on average, were stocked in Red Butte creek on October 31st. A quantity of 2000 Bonneville cutthroat trout, 3.18 inches in length on average, were stocked in Red Butte Reservoir on October 31st. Red Butte Reservoir is downstream of the entire research reach. More information can be found at https://dwrapps.utah.gov/fishstocking/Fish.

dateRemarks: Date is an estimate based on first observation of species within the NEON sampling reach. Date of first colonization was likely earlier than this first observation.
remarks: First observation of this invasive plant (AZ state noxious weed) at SYCA. Only a single plant was observed at this time.

Observations of this invasive plant have drastically increased in recent weeks. The first sighting was in 2019, and now the plant has spread across much of the site in open areas, along the stream banks, and is heavily present on the access/parking area for NEON.
